ZH: 我的记忆力很好，能够轻松记住很多东西。
EN: My memory is very good and I can easily remember a lot of things.

ZH: 他失去了部分记忆，不再记得过去发生的事情。
EN: He lost some of his memory and no longer remembers what happened in the past.

ZH: 刚才我只是一时记不住你的名字，现在想起来了。
EN: I just couldn't remember your name for a moment earlier, but now I recall.

ZH: 这个地方让我瞬间想起了小时候的记忆。
EN: This place instantly brings back memories of my childhood.

ZH: 他坚持用纸和笔做笔记，因为他相信这样更有助于记忆。
EN: He insists on taking notes with pen and paper because he believes it helps with memory.

ZH: 这些照片勾起了我关于那次旅行的美好记忆。
EN: These photos evoke fond memories of that trip.

ZH: 每个人的记忆都是独一无二的，打开了心灵的时间胶囊。
EN: Everyone's memory is unique, opening a time capsule of the mind.

ZH: 她的记忆里还保存着祖父给她的故事。
EN: She still holds the stories her grandfather told her in her memory.

ZH: 这本书很有趣，讲述了关于记忆和遗忘的故事。
EN: This book is fascinating, it tells stories about memory and forgetting.

ZH: 梦境中的记忆常常让我们感到迷惑。
EN: Memories in dreams often leave us confused.

ZH: 他的记忆力衰退了很多，经常忘记他刚刚说的话。
EN: His memory has declined a lot, often forgetting what he just said.

ZH: 这个城市给了我太多美好的记忆。
EN: This city has given me too many wonderful memories.

ZH: 那个地方带给我一些不太愉快的回忆。
EN: That place brings back some not-so-pleasant memories.

ZH: 这首歌的旋律让我想起了过去的记忆。
EN: The melody of this song reminds me of past memories.

ZH: 你有没有遇到过记忆模糊的情况？
EN: Have you ever experienced situations of blurred memory?

ZH: 家庭照片是记忆中最宝贵的见证之一。
EN: Family photos are one of the most precious witnesses in memory.

ZH: 学习新的语言对记忆有益处。
EN: Learning a new language is beneficial for memory.

ZH: 他的死让我永远留在心头的记忆。
EN: His death left a memory in my heart forever.

ZH: 那天晚上的事情我将永远铭记在心中的记忆。
EN: The events of that night will forever be etched in my memory.

ZH: 我们应该珍惜每个美好的记忆，因为它们是一生中的宝藏。
EN: We should cherish every beautiful memory, as they are treasures throughout life.
